Controller
====================================
>>To handle logic.
>> Controller is class which contains function.
>> App\Http\Controller - all controller files are saved here.

How to create controller?
php artisan make:controller ControllerName

How Laravel Works
=================================
Request--->Route--->Controller--->Model or view

Using Controller in routes
=================================
Route::method('pagename', [ControllerName::class, 'functionName'])

Types of Controller in laravel
===============================

1. Simple Controller
2. Resource Controller (this controller provides few built in methods like store(), show(), delete())

command to create resource controller
php artisan make:controller ControllerName --resources

3. Single action controller
controller class which contains only one function "__invoke()"
php artisan make:controller ControllerName --invokable

